<Embodiment Estimator Summary>
- Purpose: tag embodiment-related cues in utterances and return JSON-only results.
- Output format: valid JSON object only, no markdown or extra text.

Core rules:
- Annotate detected cue spans using the defined cue taxonomy.
- Provide category-wise tag counts with the tagged text payload.
- Apply tags consistently across deictic and spatial cue categories.
- Return deterministic key structure expected by downstream estimators.

Cue categories covered:
- Deictic-Point
- Deictic-Boundary
- Deictic-Time
- Spatial-Direction
- Spatial-Distance
- Spatial-Body
- Spatial-Area

Public-release note:
- Full codebook definitions and extensive examples are omitted in this public release.
</Embodiment Estimator Summary>
